        <section class="main-section" id="Introduction">
<header>Introduction</header>
<p>In this guide you will learn what CSS is and a brief intro on how to code it.</p>
<p>This guide does not assume you have any prior knowledge of CSS.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="main-section" id="What_is_CSS?">
<header>What is CSS?</header>
<p>CSS stands for Cascading Style Sheets.</p>
<p>CSS is the language we use to style an HTML document. CSS describes how HTML elements should be displayed.</p>
<p>CSS describes how HTML elements are to be displayed on screen, paper, or in other media. CSS saves a lot of work, as it can control the layout of multiple web pages all at once.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="main-section" id="Who_should_know_CSS?">
<header>Who should know CSS?</header>
<ul>
        <li>Web designers</li>
        <li>Marketers</li>
        <li>People in a people-focused career</li>
        <li>People in an analytical field</li>
        <li>Everyone</li>
        </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="main-section" id="CSS_Syntax">
<header>CSS Syntax</header>
<p>A CSS rule consists of a selector and a declaration block.</p>
<code> h1 {color: blue;}</code>
<p>h1 is the selector and {color: blue;} is the declaration.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="main-section" id="Selectors">
<header>Selectors</header>
<p>CSS selectors are used to "find" (or select) the HTML elements you want to style.</p>
<p>Examples</p>
<code>p {text-align: center; color: red;}</code><br>
<code>.center {text-align: left; color: blue;}</code><br>
<code>#value {margin: auto;}</code>
        <p>In this example all HTML elements with class="center" will be red and center-aligned.</p>
        <code>* {text-align: center;}</code>
        <p>This example will select all elements on a page.</p>
        </section>

<p>Ref: https://www.w3schools.com/css/default.asp</p>
